==Cover versions==
* In May 1971, singer [[Matt Monro]] released a UK single of "Isn't It a Pity" (ironically, produced by George Martin).<ref name="Clayson p 296">Clayson, ''George Harrison'', p. 296.</ref>
* Nicky Thomas recorded the song for his 1971 album ''Tell It Like It Is''.<ref name="SecondHand">[http://www.secondhandsongs.com/work/4255 "Isn't It a Pity" <U+2212> George Harrison], Second Hand Songs (retrieved 19 September 2012).</ref>
* Ireland's 1970 [[Eurovision Song Contest]] winner, [[Dana Rosemary Scallon|Dana]], covered the song in 1971, a rendition that has been described as a "poignant" commentary to the [[Bloody Sunday (1972)|political upheaval]] then gripping [[Ulster]].<ref name="Clayson p 296" />
* [[The Three Degrees]] recorded "Isn't It a Pity" during their period on [[Roulette Records]] in 1970<U+2212>72, later released on the 1995 compilation ''The Roulette Years''.<ref>Andrew Hamilton, [http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-roulette-years-mw0000372428 "The Three Degrees ''The Roulette Years''], [[Allmusic]] (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* [[Nina Simone]]'s "intense", eleven-minute reworking of "Isn't It a Pity" was released on her 1972 album ''[[Emergency Ward (album)|Emergency Ward!]]'', a statement on the [[Vietnam War]] which also includes a cover of "My Sweet Lord".<ref name=ward>Mark Richardson, [http://www.allmusic.com/album/emergency-ward%21-mw0000371066 "Nina Simone ''Emergency Ward!''"], [[Allmusic]] (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref> A six-minute version of "Isn't It a Pity" was issued on the 51-track compilation ''The Essential Nina Simone'' in 1993.<ref>Ron Wynn, [http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-essential-nina-simone-mw0000102261 "Nina Simone ''The Essential Nina Simone''"], [[Allmusic]] (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref> In his [[I, Me, Mine (book)|autobiography]], Harrison admits to having been influenced by Simone's treatment when he came to record his 1975 song "[[The Answer's at the End]]".<ref>Harrison, p. 300.</ref>
* [[Galaxie 500]] covered the song on their ''[[On Fire (Galaxie 500 album)|'On Fire]]'' album in 1989.<ref name="GH covers" />
* A version by [[Pete Drake]] appeared on his eponymous solo album, released in 1997.<ref>[http://expectingrain.com/dok/who/d/drakepete.html Drake, Pete], Expecting Rain (retrieved 19 September 2012).</ref>
* The song appears on [[Television Personalities]]' 1998 album ''Don't Cry Baby ... It's Only a Movie''.<ref name="GH covers" />
* In March 2001, [[18th Dye]] contributed a version of "Isn't It a Pity" to ''Snowstorm <U+2212> A Tribute to Galaxie 500''.<ref name="SecondHand" />
* At the [[Concert for George]] on 29 November 2002, a year to the day after Harrison's death, Eric Clapton and Billy Preston performed the song with backing from [[Dhani Harrison]], [[Jeff Lynne]], [[Gary Brooker]], [[Jim Keltner]], [[Ray Cooper]], [[Jim Horn]], [[Tom Scott (musician)|Tom Scott]] and others.<ref>Stephen Thomas Erlewine, [http://www.allmusic.com/album/concert-for-george-mw0000329292 "Original Soundtrack: ''Concert for George''"], [[Allmusic]] (retrieved 4 August 2012).</ref>
* [[Jay Bennett]] and [[Edward Burch]] recorded "Isn't It a Pity" for ''Songs from the Material World: A Tribute to George'', a multi-artist compilation released in February 2003.<ref>Johnny Loftus, [http://www.allmusic.com/album/songs-from-the-material-world-a-tribute-to-george-harrison-mw0000019300 "Various Artists: ''Songs from the Material World: A Tribute to George''], Allmusic (retrieved 6 July 2012).</ref>
* Classical guitarist Joseph Breznikar recorded a version of the song for his 2003 tribute album ''George Harrison Remembered: A Touch of Class''.<ref name="Breznikar">[http://www.secondhandsongs.com/release/50957 ''George Harrison Remembered: A Touch of Class'' <U+2212> Joseph Breznikar], Second Hand Songs (retrieved 19 September 2012).</ref>
* [[Cowboy Junkies]] covered the song on their ''[[Early 21st Century Blues]]'' album in 2005.<ref name="SecondHand" />
* Joel Harrison recorded "Isn't It a Pity" for his album ''Harrison on Harrison: Jazz Explanations of George Harrison'', released in October 2005.<ref>[http://www.secondhandsongs.com/release/13973 ''Harrison on Harrison: Jazz Explanations of George Harrison'' <U+2212> Joel Harrison], Second Hand Songs (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* A cover version by [[Les Fradkin]] was released in 2005 on his ''Something for George'' tribute album.<ref>[http://www.lesfradkin.com/products-group-39.html George Harrison/Beatles Vocal Tribute CDs], lesfradkin.com (retrieved 16 October 2012).</ref>
* Spanish singer Rafo de la Cuba covered the song in December 2005.<ref>[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7FAeVPsBi8M "Tributo Beatles <U+2212> Isn<U+00B4>t it a Pity"], YouTube (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* A version by [[Paul Young]] was included on his 2006 album ''Rock Swings''.<ref name="GH covers" />
* [[Pedro Aznar]] covered the song as "No Es Una Pena?", with Spanish lyrics, on his album ''Quebrado'' in 2008.<ref>[http://www.secondhandsongs.com/performance/92497 "No Es Una Pena?"], Second Hand Songs (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* In September 2008, members of Heard of Buffalo performed the song for the [[MDA Show of Strength|Jerry Lewis MDA Telethon]].<ref>[http://wn.com/isn't_it_a_pity_cover_song_by_george_harrison_performed_by_randy_michael_from_heard_of_buffalo Jerry Lewis MDA 2008 Telethon: Randy and Michael from Heard of Buffalo performing "Isn't It a Pity"], wn.com (retrieved 4 August 2012).</ref>
* "Isn't It a Pity" was among a number of Harrison and Beatle covers recorded or performed by [[Elliott Smith]];<ref>David Greenwald, [http://www.rawkblog.net/2009/02/elliott-smith-the-complete-live-covers/ Elliott Smith <U+2212> The Complete Live Covers], Rawkblog, 24 February 2009 (retrieved 4 August 2012).</ref> a version appears on the ''1998-08-12: Hoboken, NJ, USA'' album.<ref name="GH covers">[http://www.coversproject.com/artist/george%20harrison/ George Harrison Cover Songs], The Covers Project (retrieved 4 August 2012).</ref>
* [[Soul music|Soul]] singer [[Bettye LaVette]] covered the song on ''Interpretations: The British Rock Songbook'' in 2010.<ref>[http://www.bettyelavette.com/cd-releases.html CD Releases], bettyelavette.com (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* David McAlmont and Bernard Butler's performance of "Isn't It a Pity" was released on the ''Live From Leicester Square'' album in February 2011.<ref name="SecondHand" />
* A version by Jonathan Wilson and [[Graham Nash]] appeared on ''Harrison Covered'', a tribute CD accompanying the November 2011 issue of ''[[Mojo (magazine)|Mojo]]'' magazine.<ref>[http://www.secondhandsongs.com/release/67333 ''Harrison Covered''], Second Hand Songs (retrieved 16 September 2012).</ref>
* Also in November 2011, marking the ten-year anniversary of Harrison's death, [[Keane (band)|Keane]] recorded a version of the song.<ref>[http://www.keanemusic.com/archive-comment.php?rnd=QUnBFOTLg8jJ2F3aHcxnfo6xkW93lelAFzszcBFx698= "Isn't It a Pity (George Harrison cover)"], KEANE (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>
* [[Roberta Flack]] covered "Isn't It a Pity" on her album ''Let It Be Roberta <U+2212> Roberta Flack Sings The Beatles'', released in February 2012.<ref name="SecondHand" />
* [[My Morning Jacket]] have included "Isn't It a Pity" in their live performances; when playing the song at the [[Forecastle Festival]] in July 2012, they were joined on stage by [[Dean Wareham]] of Galaxie 500.<ref>[http://www.youaintnopicasso.com/2012/07/16/mp3s-my-morning-jacket-cover-george-harrison-george-michael-at-forecastle/ "My Morning Jacket cover George Harrison, George Michael at Forecastle"], youaintnopicasso.com (retrieved 20 September 2012).</ref>

